Good sci-fi platform puzzle game, with a pretty surprisingly interesting and thought-provoking story.

Pros:
- Great graphics;
- Great sound design;
- Excellent and fun puzzles (you will catch yourself imagining your clones walking alongside you in real life after finishing this game xP, as well as see upside down clones on this text)
- Interesting lore and story;
- That ending.

Cons:
- Not really any con. Maybe that the achievements are almost impossible to get without looking them up, if you care about that?
- Pretty short, but puzzles are difficult to design, so that makes sense
